data.title: NSW Labor majority govt could work ‘efficiently’ in dealing with state health concerns
data.meta_description:
A Labor majority could work more “efficiently” in dealing with state concerns over health issues, says Chief Advocate for National Seniors Ian Henschke.

“I think there’s an opportunity there for the federal government to talk to the states and say can we do things better and more efficiently in health,” said Mr Henschke.

“At the moment with aged care issues, a lot of older Australians are in the hospital system when they should actually be looked after better in an aged care home and sometimes they’re being moved from an aged care home into the hospital system – so it’s a lot of cost-shifting going on.

“There’s great opportunities there at the moment – for the federal government and the states to sit down and say let’s look at that.”
